    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of native Americans who were living along the Pearl River between Louisiana and Mississippi when Europeans arrived in 1702. Were gradually assimilated into the Houma and Bayogoula tribes in the mid-1700s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
